cipal in the authorization attributes as JSON. After an external-OIDC login that principal is a DhisOidcUser wrapping a UserDetailsImpl, neither of which is on Spring Security's SecurityJackson2Modules deserialization allowlist, so any read of such an authorization (e.g. the /oauth2/token exchange) failed with HTTP 500: \"... is not in the allowlist\". Serialization succeeded, which is why the failure only showed up on read.\n\nRegister Dhis2OAuth2PrincipalJackson2Module on the authorization service's ObjectMapper to allowlist and (de)serialize both types, and make UserDetailsImpl round-trip cleanly through its Lombok builder (@Jacksonized) instead of the previous hand-written, never-exercised @JsonCreator factory.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e","author":{"name":"Morten Svanaes","email":"msvanaes@dhis2.org"},"id":"2adf21c0e36b9f1b51652f33bf97cd1e83457e09","tree_id":"467917c946241fce957283a5fc207397d8bfaa41","timestamp":"2026-05-31T04:45:59Z","committer":{"name":"Morten Svanaes","email":"msvanaes@dhis2.org"}},"workflow_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/dhis2/dhis2-core/actions/workflows/5591308","repository":{"id":66940520,"node_id":"MDEwOlJlcG9zaXRvcnk2Njk0MDUyMA==","owner":{"login":"dhis2","id":1089987,"node_id":"MDEyOk9yZ2FuaXphdGlvbjEwODk5ODc=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1089987?v=4","html_url":"https://github.com/dhis2","gravatar_id":"","type":"Organization","site_admin":false,"url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/events{/privacy}","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/following{/other_user}","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/followers","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/gists{/gist_id}","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/orgs","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/received_events","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/dhis2/repos","starred_u